---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout>
	<!-- Article header -->
	<section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 pt-14 pb-8">
		<a
			href="journal.html"
			class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-mono text-stone hover:text-camel transition-colors mb-8"
		>
			← Back to journal
		</a>
		<div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-5">
			<span
				class="text-xs font-semibold text-sage border border-sage px-2.5 py-1 uppercase tracking-wide"
				>Food & Culture</span
			>
			<span class="font-mono text-xs text-stone"
				>Jun 14, 2026 · 21 min read</span
			>
		</div>
		<h1 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-5xl leading-[1.1]">
			I ate at 40 street food stalls in Vietnam. Here's the honest
			ranking.
		</h1>
		<p class="mt-5 text-lg text-espresso/65 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
			From a plastic-stool pho spot in Hanoi's old quarter to a banh
			mi cart that costs less than a dollar — a real eater's guide
			with no affiliate links and no sponsored meals.
		</p>
		<p class="font-mono text-xs text-stone mt-6">
			21.0°N · 105.8°E — HANOI, VIETNAM
		</p>
	</section>

	<!-- Cover image -->
	<section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 mb-12">
		<img
			src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1555400038-63f5ba517a47?w=1200&q=85"
			alt="Street food stall at night in Vietnam"
			class="w-full h-112 object-cover"
		/>
		<p class="text-xs font-mono text-stone mt-3">
			Old Quarter night market, Hanoi. 9pm on a Tuesday — busiest it
			ever gets.
		</p>
	</section>

	<!-- Article content + sidebar -->
	<section
		class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 pb-16 grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_280px] gap-16"
	>
		<!-- Body -->
		<article class="prose max-w-2xl">
			<p class="text-lg">
				Let me be honest about how this started: I ran out of
				restaurant money in Hanoi on day three. Not because I
				overspent — because the first place I walked into
				charged $14 for a bowl of pho, and I knew that was
				wrong. So I left, found a plastic stool two streets
				away, paid 35,000 dong (about $1.40), and ate the best
				soup I've had in my life.
			</p>

			<p>
				That was the beginning of a fairly obsessive three
				weeks. I ended up eating almost exclusively from street
				stalls and market counters across Hanoi, Hoi An, and Ho
				Chi Minh City — 40 spots in total, tracked in a notes
				app with prices, what I ordered, and a one-sentence
				verdict.
			</p>

			<blockquote>
				The places with handwritten menus and plastic stools
				almost always beat the ones with laminated photos and
				English out front. Not always. But almost always.
			</blockquote>

			<h2>North: Hanoi</h2>
			<p>
				Hanoi is a pho city. Not bun bo hue, not banh mi — pho.
				And the version you get here is noticeably different
				from what I'd had elsewhere: cleaner broth, lighter
				spice, a kind of quiet confidence that doesn't need to
				announce itself. The best bowl I found was at a spot
				near Hoan Kiem lake that opens at 6am and closes when
				they run out, usually around 9.
			</p>

			<p>
				Budget reality check for Hanoi: you can eat breakfast,
				lunch, and dinner for under $5 if you're eating from
				stalls. Comfortably. A banh mi is 15,000–25,000 dong.
				Pho runs 35,000–50,000. Bun cha — the dish Obama
				famously ate here — is 40,000–60,000. These aren't the
				tourist prices; they're the real ones from spots where I
				was often the only foreigner.
			</p>

			<h2>Central: Hoi An</h2>
			<p>
				Hoi An is beautiful and increasingly crowded, but the
				food is genuinely its own thing — cao lau, white rose
				dumplings, and banh mi that's legitimately different
				from the Saigon version (softer bread, more
				pork-forward). The tourist trap density is real, but the
				market on Tran Phu is still mostly locals eating lunch,
				and the prices reflect that.
			</p>
		</article>

		<!-- Sidebar -->
		<aside class="lg:sticky lg:top-24 lg:self-start space-y-8">
			<!-- Trip summary card -->
			<div class="bg-espresso text-cream p-6">
				<p
					class="font-mono text-xs text-stone tracking-widest mb-4"
				>
					TRIP SNAPSHOT
				</p>
				<ul class="space-y-3 text-sm">
					<li
						class="flex justify-between border-b border-stone/20 pb-3"
					>
						<span class="text-cream/60">Duration</span>
						<span class="font-medium">21 days</span>
					</li>
					<li
						class="flex justify-between border-b border-stone/20 pb-3"
					>
						<span class="text-cream/60">Cities</span>
						<span class="font-medium"
							>Hanoi, Hoi An, HCMC</span
						>
					</li>
					<li
						class="flex justify-between border-b border-stone/20 pb-3"
					>
						<span class="text-cream/60"
							>Food budget/day</span
						>
						<span class="font-medium text-camel"
							>$4–7</span
						>
					</li>
					<li class="flex justify-between">
						<span class="text-cream/60"
							>Stalls visited</span
						>
						<span class="font-medium">40</span>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<!-- YouTube callout -->
			<div class="border border-stone/40 p-6">
				<p
					class="font-mono text-xs text-stone tracking-widest mb-3"
				>
					WATCH THE VIDEO
				</p>
				<div style="aspect-ratio:16/9" class="w-full mb-4">
					<iframe
						class="w-full h-full"
						src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/dQw4w9WgXcQ"
						title="Vietnam street food video"
						frameborder="0"
						allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
						allowfullscreen></iframe>
				</div>
				<p class="text-sm text-espresso/60 leading-relaxed">
					The full 24-hour street food challenge is on the
					channel — with prices and exact locations.
				</p>
			</div>

			<!-- Tags -->
			<div>
				<p
					class="font-mono text-xs text-stone tracking-widest mb-3"
				>
					TAGS
				</p>
				<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
					<span
						class="text-xs bg-espresso/8 px-3 py-1.5 font-mono"
						>#vietnam</span
					>
					<span
						class="text-xs bg-espresso/8 px-3 py-1.5 font-mono"
						>#food</span
					>
					<span
						class="text-xs bg-espresso/8 px-3 py-1.5 font-mono"
						>#budget</span
					>
					<span
						class="text-xs bg-espresso/8 px-3 py-1.5 font-mono"
						>#streetfood</span
					>
					<span
						class="text-xs bg-espresso/8 px-3 py-1.5 font-mono"
						>#southeast-asia</span
					>
				</div>
			</div>
		</aside>
	</section>

	<!-- More posts -->
	<section class="bg-cream border-t border-stone/30">
		<div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-16">
			<h2 class="font-serif text-2xl mb-10">Keep reading</h2>
			<div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
				<a href="article.html" class="group">
					<img
						src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1533105079780-92b9be482077?w=600&q=80"
						alt="Beach"
						class="w-full h-44 object-cover group-hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity"
					/>
					<p
						class="font-mono text-xs text-camel uppercase tracking-wide mt-4 mb-2"
					>
						Budget Tips
					</p>
					<h3
						class="font-serif text-lg leading-snug group-hover:text-camel transition-colors"
					>
						How I travel full-time for under $1,200 a
						month
					</h3>
				</a>
				<a href="article.html" class="group">
					<img
						src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1524492412937-b28074a5d7da?w=600&q=80"
						alt="Temple"
						class="w-full h-44 object-cover group-hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity"
					/>
					<p
						class="font-mono text-xs text-sage uppercase tracking-wide mt-4 mb-2"
					>
						Off the Path
					</p>
					<h3
						class="font-serif text-lg leading-snug group-hover:text-camel transition-colors"
					>
						Hampi before the crowds: what I saw at 5am
					</h3>
				</a>
				<a href="article.html" class="group">
					<img
						src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1467269204594-9661b134dd2b?w=600&q=80"
						alt="Street"
						class="w-full h-44 object-cover group-hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity"
					/>
					<p
						class="font-mono text-xs text-camel uppercase tracking-wide mt-4 mb-2"
					>
						Solo Travel
					</p>
					<h3
						class="font-serif text-lg leading-snug group-hover:text-camel transition-colors"
					>
						The loneliness nobody talks about
					</h3>
				</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>
